history.content:
Yes, being enrolled in CogSci126 will prevent you from getting off the waitlist for CompSci188.

This is the sort of thing that the new Swap feature is supposed to be for (i.e. exactly what you want), although since you didn't waitlist for CompSci188 via Swap, I'm presuming that this is too late as information for you this time.

Alternatively, you could wait until you're near the top of the waitlist for 188 before dropping 126.
yes yes and yes. Please view pinned post about conflicts

I have a question about my situation with course enrollment conflicts, that is probably different than most. I am currently enrolled in cog sci 126 and waitlisted in cs 188, which have a lecture conflict. HOWEVER, cog sci 126 is a backup for me if i don't get into cs 188, i.e. if I get into CS 188 I will drop cog sci 126 (so no conflict). 

My concern is that I want to stay enrolled in cog sci 126 until I am definitely enrolled in CS 188 (I am fairly confident I will be based on the discussion section I am waitlisted in), and only then drop cog sci 126. However, will I have a problem enrolling into cs 188 if I am enrolled in cog sci 126, even though I plan to immediately drop it once I am enrolled in cs 188? Will staying enrolled in cog sci 126 (my backup to cs 188) prevent me from actually being enrolled in cs 188? This feels a bit like a catch-22 situation. Any advice/help would be appreciated!
